Description:
    List and update VSCode extensions.

Usage:
    code-ext --list
    code-ext
        List all VSCode extensions currently installed
    code-ext --refresh
        Refresh and update .extensions file with any new installed extension in VSCode, which is currently missing in the file.
    code-ext --update
        If any of the extensions listed in the .extension file is missing in the VSCode setup, it installs that extension.
    code-ext --help
        Shows the help contents.

Examples:
    code-ext
    code-ext --list
    code-ext --refresh
    code-ext --update
    code-ext --help


